</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="3" style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; color: black; background-color: lawngreen"><i>Scots</i>, <i>Lallans</i></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Spoken in</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Scotland" title="Scotland">Scotland</a>, <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland" title="Northern Ireland">Northern Ireland</a>, <a href="/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland" title="Republic of Ireland">Republic of Ireland</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Region</th>
<td colspan="2"><span class="flagicon"><a href="/wiki/Scotland" title="Scotland"><img alt="Scotland" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/Flag_of_Scotland.svg/22px-Flag_of_Scotland.svg.png" width="22" height="13" class="thumbborder" /></a></span> Scotland: <a href="/wiki/Scottish_Lowlands" title="Scottish Lowlands">Scottish Lowlands</a>, <a href="/wiki/Northern_Isles" title="Northern Isles">Northern Isles</a>, <a href="/wiki/Caithness" title="Caithness">Caithness</a>.<br />
<span class="flagicon"><a href="/wiki/Ulster" title="Ulster"><img alt="Ulster" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Flag_of_Ulster.svg/22px-Flag_of_Ulster.svg.png" width="22" height="15" class="thumbborder" /></a></span> Ulster: Counties <a href="/wiki/County_Down" title="County Down">Down</a>, <a href="/wiki/County_Antrim" title="County Antrim">Antrim</a>, <a href="/wiki/County_Londonderry" title="County Londonderry">Londonderry</a>, <a href="/wiki/County_Donegal" title="County Donegal">Donegal</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Total speakers</th>
<td colspan="2">est. 200,000 <small>(<a href="http://www.ethnologue.com/show_country.asp?name=GB" class="external text" rel="nofollow">ethnologue</a>)</small> to over 1.5 million <small>(<a href="/wiki/General_Register_Office_for_Scotland" title="General Register Office for Scotland">General Register Office for Scotland</a>, 1996)</small>
<p>A <a href="/wiki/Scottish_Government" title="Scottish Government">Scottish Government</a> study found that 85% of respondents (being a representative sample of Scotland's adult population) claim to speak Scots to varying degrees<sup id="cite_ref-Public_Attitudes_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Public_Attitudes-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><a href="/wiki/Language_family" title="Language family">Language family</a></th>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:left"><a href="/wiki/Indo-European_languages" title="Indo-European languages">Indo-European</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:15px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="/wiki/Germanic_languages" title="Germanic languages">Germanic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="/wiki/West_Germanic_languages" title="West Germanic languages">West Germanic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="/wiki/Anglo-Frisian_languages" title="Anglo-Frisian languages">Anglo-Frisian</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="/wiki/English_languages" title="English languages">Anglic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
